Condensed Milk Shortbread
Buttery shortbread with condensed milk richness
classic
Sweet, Hard, Buttery

INGREDIENTS:
2 3/4 cups all-purpose flour
1 cup butter (2 sticks)
7 fl oz condensed milk (1/2 can)
3/4 cup white sugar
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1 tbsp pumpkin spice (optional)

INSTRUCTIONS:
Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
Beat butter and sugar with mixer until smooth and fluffy
Add condensed milk and vanilla; beat until well blended
Add flour, baking powder and pumpkin spice if using; beat until combined
Form tablespoon-sized dough balls and place 2in apart on sheet
Bake just until cookies lose their shiny appearance, about 12 minutes
Let cookies cool for 10 minutes before removing. Makes 40-50 cookies